hoes white with dust. He rested on all the benches and once or twice plucked a blackberry, grimacing from the sourness. While walking along the highway he noticed a fair-haired small boy following him with tiny steps, holding an empty beer bottle in his hands, and lagging behind on purpose and staring at him with unbearable childish concentration.

Luzhin halted. The boy also halted. Luzhin moved, the boy moved.

Then Luzhin lost his temper and threatened him with his cane. The other froze, grin